briefTitle: Safety, Tolerability and Immunogenicity of Novartis Meningococcal B Recombinant Vaccine Administered to Healthy Adolescents According to Different Vaccination Schedules

outcomeMeasures.title: Percentages of Subjects With hSBA Titer ≥1:4 After Receiving One, Two or Three Doses of rMenB+OMV NZ Vaccine.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the percentage of subjects with hSBA titter \>1:4 against 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254 strains at months 1, 2, 3.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Local Reactions and Systemic Reactions Occurring in Days 1 to 7 After Vaccination
outcomeMeasures.description: Safety was assessed as the number of subjects who reported local and systemic reactions during day 1 to day 7 after any vaccination with rMenB+OMV

outcomeMeasures.title: Percentages of Subjects With hSBA Titer ≥1:4 After Receiving a Booster Dose of rMenB+OMV NZ Vaccine at Month 6.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the percentage of subjects with hSBA titter \>1:4 agains 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254 strains at months 6 \& 7.

outcomeMeasures.title: Percentage of Subjects With hSBA Titer ≥1:8 After Primary and Booster Vaccination.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the percentage of subjects with hSBA titer ≥1:8 against 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254 strains.

outcomeMeasures.title: Percentages of Subjects With at Least a Fourfold Rise in hSBA Titer Over the Prevaccination and After Booster Vaccination.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the percentage of subjects with at least a fourfold rise in hSBA titer over the prevaccination and after booster vaccination against 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254 strains at month-1, month-2, month-3 and month-7.

outcomeMeasures.title: Geometric Mean Titers (GMTs) After Primary and Booster Vaccination.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the Geometric mean titers (GMTs) after primary and booster vaccination against 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254.

outcomeMeasures.title: Geometric Mean Ratios (GMRs) After Primary and Booster Vaccination.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the Geometric mean ratios (GMRs) after primary and booster vaccination against 44/76-SL, 5/99, NZ98/254.

outcomeMeasures.title: GMCs of Antibodies Against 287-953Antigen (ELISA) After Primary and Booster Vaccination.
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the Geometric mean Concentration (GMCs) after primary and booster vaccination against Antigen 287-953 Antigen.

outcomeMeasures.title: GMRs of Antibodies Against 287-953Antigen (ELISA) After Primary and Booster Vaccination
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the Geometric mean Ratios (GMRs) after primary and booster vaccination against 287-953Antigen

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects Reporting Unsolicited AEs Throughout the Study.
outcomeMeasures.description: Safety was assessed as the number of subjects who reported unsolicited AEs throughout the study.

outcomeMeasures.title: Percentage of Subjects With hSBA Titers≥4 After Receiving Second Dose of Vaccination
outcomeMeasures.description: Immunogenicity was evaluated by measuring the percentage of subjects with hSBA titter \>1:4 against M10713 strain at 1 month after second dose of vaccination (Month 3)
